Preconditions:
The method leastOpsExpressTarget should be a public method.
The method should have two integer parameters: x and target.
The division operator (/) should return rational numbers.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the least number of operators used to form an expression that equals the given target.
The expression formed should use the least number of operators possible.
The expression formed should be valid and evaluate to the given target.
The expression formed should only use the division operator (/) and other necessary operators to reach the target.
The expression formed should be in a valid format and syntax according to Java programming language.